A vintage 1950s-style illustration of a mechanic in oil-stained overalls standing before an elaborate, impossibly complex machine with gears, levers, pipes, and dials sprawling in every direction. The mechanic scratches their head in bewilderment while holding a single small wrench, clearly inadequate for the task. The machine has sections that appear to be working against each other—some parts spinning clockwise while connected parts spin counter-clockwise, steam escaping from misaligned joints. The color palette features muted browns, creams, and rust oranges with occasional pops of teal. The scene conveys the feeling of a small fix causing unexpected cascading problems throughout an intricate system.
